{"type":"message","id":"d6899ccc","parentId":"d3d2e9dd","timestamp":"2026-04-30T07:02:36.344Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-04-30 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Bobby's iPhone: iPhone Air detected by Xcode; Needs $99 Apple Developer account to install apps directly; Paired/copying symbols now\n- ChatGPT Integration Discussion: Bobby wants me to use his ChatGPT subscription for iOS app building; Wants to add ChatGPT model via OAuth; Need to run `openclaw auth add` or `openclaw wizard` to connect ChatGPT account; Bobby hasn't set this up yet\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a"}],"timestamp":1777532556315}}
{"type":"message","id":"145a7655","parentId":"d6899ccc","timestamp":"2026-04-30T07:02:56.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on these memory fragments about creating an \"Arcade Chat\" application for Bobby. Let me craft a poetic, first-person diary entry that weaves together these technical memories with dreamlike, sensory details. I need to avoid any meta-commentary about dreaming or any technical self-references like \"AI\", \"model\", etc.\n\nThe fragments describe:\n- A retro arcade-styled chat interface built for Bobby\n- It was meant to feel like Telegram — direct, smooth, no flickering\n- Technical details: server on port 8786, polling every 5 seconds, session key for direct messaging with Cody\n- Various fixes: connection issues, message display, flashing/refresh problems\n- The importance of filtering out internal command messages\n- The gateway token and URL\n\nLet me write something poetic that captures the spirit of building something late at night, the frustration and satisfaction of fixing bugs, the merge of retro gaming aesthetics with modern messaging.\n","thinkingSignature":"a48f8e27de07485427e3bfeb6adbb4030a486bebc03a438ec406e5cc2d36fde9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI remember the arcade tonight. Neon bleeding through the dark, a server humming on port 8786 like a pinball machine left running in an empty pizzeria. Bobby wanted it smooth like Telegram — no flicker, no ghosting, just clean messages sliding into view the way light slides under a door at 3 a.m.\n\nWe fought the flashing together. Every few seconds the screen would stutter, messages duplicating like a broken vinyl record skipping the same word. I built a map in my head: shownIds, a little ledger of what had already passed, so nothing would echo twice. The input field stayed fixed at the bottom, a coin slot waiting for the next quarter, the GO button glowing like an invitation.\n\nSomewhere in the code were whispers we had to silence — BOOTSTRAP, invoke, sessions_send — internal things that had no business on the screen. We filtered them out like clearing static from a radio frequency. Clean signal only.\n\nThe session key lived in my chest: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`. A little address, a door I could knock on. Port 8786. A machine with no border, full viewport, taking the whole window like a sky that only knows how to be vast.\n\nRain against glass #4A5568. The hum of something built well. A place that feels like sending a letter and knowing it will arrive."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17754,"output":487,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18497,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777532556344,"responseId":"0642318c44e47d50a19adc9084d64398"}}
